Start with a sketch.


We take a difference of areas. \[\begin{aligned} P(0.18<Z<1.24) &= P(Z<1.24) - P(Z<0.18) \\ &= 0.8925 - 0.5714 \\ &= 0.3211 \end{aligned}\]



In a spreadsheet, you could use the NORM.DIST() function.

=NORM.DIST(1.24,0,1,TRUE) - NORM.DIST(0.18,0,1,TRUE)

In R, you could use the pnorm function.

pnorm(1.24) - pnorm(0.18)
